<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#800000">Originally posted by Andadas on 05-16-2000 03:26 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I run around with a 201 INT and 251 Charisma lately.  Guess what?  I can mez and charm far better than my companions with there 160 - 200 CHA!

I am never the "buff *****" enchanter on a raid, because nobody needs two enchanters to mez when ONE can do it.  And it is very hard for me to be the only one when I have less than 200 CHA.  

Sure, you can say this is speculation, but to those who group with me and say "Normally we need 3 enchanters to do this, how are you doing it", I can only answer "I have a HIGH CHA and I am not some idiot 16 year old kid and I didn't power level my character up"  

The most important stats to an enchanter are without ANY doubt in my mind CHARISMA, Armor Class, Hit Points, Intelligence, and Agility.

And anybody who knows me, will vouch that I am damn good at what I do... namely MEZ and CHARM!

Semper Fidelis,

Andadas de'Infierno
52nd Enchanter
Brell Serilis

P.S.  None of that was bragging, just facts put forward to help the original posted and anybody else wanting REAL advice from a REAL enchanter  :)
</TEXTAREA>
